<p>I am having problem with angular validation. <br> this one does'nt work...</p>  <pre><code>&lt;input type="text" ng-model="text1" name="text1" required&gt; &lt;span ng-show="text1.$error.required"&gt;Please enter something!&lt;/span&gt; </code></pre>  <p>but this works:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;form name="myform"&gt; &lt;input type="text" ng-model="text1" name="text1" required&gt; &lt;span ng-show="myform.text1.$error.required"&gt;Please enter something!&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/form&gt; </code></pre>  <p>is it possible to somehow correct the first one without placing it inside a form?</p>  <p>thanks</p>